{"id":"sheshbazzar","term":"Sheshbazzar","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>O sun-god, defend the lord! (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 1:8\">Ezra 1:8</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 1:11\">11</a>), probably another name for Zerubbabel (q.v.), <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:2\">Ezra 2:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Haggai 1:12\">Hag. 1:12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Haggai 1:14\">14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 4:6\">Zech. 4:6</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Zechariah 4:10\">10</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Ezra 1:8","Ezra 1:11","Ezra 2:2","Haggai 1:12","Haggai 1:14","Zechariah 4:6","Zechariah 4:10"]}